parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag "off" indicator is displayed
the airbag system fails to deploy in a crash
the seatbelt locks up
and the airbag sensor mat fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS can lead to the airbag system malfunctioning, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag "off" indicator is displayed
the OCS sensor mat fails
and the passenger seat sensor malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Hazard lights not turning on
tire pressure monitoring system light staying on
doors not opening
windows not rolling down
engine revving and lunging forward without input
and other electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to launch forward unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Engine revving and sputtering
sudden launching forward when backing out of a parking spot or stopped at a stop sign or red light
and transmission-related malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seat and seatbelt malfunctions can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Front seat cushion coming loose from the seat frame
seatbelt sensor shorting out
and defective airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioning and Heating System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air conditioning and heating system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Blower for the A/C or heat stopped working
and required slamming the hood to turn it back on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery and starting system malfunctions can leave the driver stranded and cause inconvenience.
symptoms: Engine failing to start
requiring jump-starting or recharging
and battery replacement not resolving the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Cruise Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the cruise control does not turn off when the brakes are applied
the engine RPMs increase while the foot is on the brake
the vehicle lunges forward and accelerates
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite applying the brakes
the cruise control does not respond to manual deactivation.
